---
/**
 * Top 10 Family Disputes Over Estates
 */
import Header from '../../../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../../../components/Footer.astro';
---

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Top 10 Family Disputes Over Estates | YourWillPro</title>
  <meta name="description" content="Money and grief are a volatile combination. These are the most common conflicts that tear families apart.">
  <link rel="icon" type="image/png" href="/ywp-logo.png">
  <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@400;500;600;700&family=Source+Serif+4:wght@400;600;700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
</head>
<body>

<Header />

<!-- Breadcrumb Navigation -->
<nav class="breadcrumb" style="padding: 1rem 2rem; font-size: 0.85rem; color: #7a7a7a; background: white; border-bottom: 1px solid #e2e2e2;">
  <a href="/" style="color: #7a7a7a; text-decoration: none;">Home</a>
  <span style="margin: 0 0.5rem;">›</span>
  <a href="/planning-tools/" style="color: #7a7a7a; text-decoration: none;">Planning Tools</a>
  <span style="margin: 0 0.5rem;">›</span>
  <a href="/planning-tools/top-10/" style="color: #7a7a7a; text-decoration: none;">Top 10</a>
  <span style="margin: 0 0.5rem;">›</span>
  <span>Family Disputes Over Estates</span>
</nav>

<main>
  <!-- Hero Section -->
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-inner">
      <div class="hero-badge">Top 10</div>
      <h1>Family Disputes Over Estates</h1>
      <p class="hero-subtitle">Money and grief are a volatile combination. These are the most common conflicts that tear families apart.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Stat Bar -->
  <section class="stat-bar">
    <div class="stat-bar-inner">
      <div class="stat-item">
        <div class="stat-number">74%</div>
        <div class="stat-label">Increase in contested wills over 10 years</div>
      </div>
      <div class="stat-item">
        <div class="stat-number">$35K+</div>
        <div class="stat-label">Average cost to contest or defend a will</div>
      </div>
      <div class="stat-item">
        <div class="stat-number">51%</div>
        <div class="stat-label">Of claims are family provision claims</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Content with Sidebar -->
  <div class="content-wrapper">

    <!-- LEFT SIDEBAR -->
    <aside class="top10-sidebar">
      <nav class="sidebar-nav">

        <!-- SECTION 1: On This Page -->
        <div class="sidebar-section">
          <h3 class="sidebar-title">On This Page</h3>
          <ul>
            <li><a href="#reason-1" class="sidebar-link"><span class="sidebar-num">1</span> Unequal shares between siblings</a></li>
            <li><a href="#reason-2" class="sidebar-link"><span class="sidebar-num">2</span> The new spouse vs the children</a></li>
            <li><a href="#reason-3" class="sidebar-link"><span class="sidebar-num">3</span> Who gets the family home</a></li>
            <li><a href="#reason-4" class="sidebar-link"><span class="sidebar-num">4</span> Executor favouring themselves</a></li>
            <li><a href="#reason-5" class="sidebar-link"><span class="sidebar-num">5</span> Sentimental items with no clear owner</a></li>
            <li><a href="#reason-6" class="sidebar-link"><span class="sidebar-num">6</span> Secret debts emerging</a></li>
            <li><a href="#reason-7" class="sidebar-link"><span class="sidebar-num">7</span> One child provided care, others didn't</a></li>
            <li><a href="#reason-8" class="sidebar-link"><span class="sidebar-num">8</span> Loans that were (or weren't) repaid</a></li>
            <li><a href="#reason-9" class="sidebar-link"><span class="sidebar-num">9</span> Business succession disputes</a></li>
            <li><a href="#reason-10" class="sidebar-link"><span class="sidebar-num">10</span> Missing or suspicious wills</a></li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- SECTION 2: More Top 10 Lists -->
        <div class="sidebar-section">
          <h3 class="sidebar-title">More Top 10 Lists</h3>
          <ul>
            <li><a href="/planning-tools/top-10/reasons-people-delay" class="sidebar-link">Reasons People Delay</a></li>
            <li><a href="/planning-tools/top-10/mistakes" class="sidebar-link">Mistakes Writing a Will</a></li>
            <li><a href="/planning-tools/top-10/reasons-wills-challenged" class="sidebar-link">Reasons Wills Are Challenged</a></li>
            <li><a href="/planning-tools/top-10/myths" class="sidebar-link">Myths About Wills</a></li>
            <li><a href="/planning-tools/top-10/when-to-update" class="sidebar-link">When to Update Your Will</a></li>
            <li><a href="/planning-tools/top-10/things-will-doesnt-do" class="sidebar-link">Things a Will Doesn't Do</a></li>
            <li><a href="/planning-tools/top-10/executor-responsibilities" class="sidebar-link">Executor Responsibilities</a></li>
            <li><a href="/planning-tools/top-10/family-disputes" class="sidebar-link active">Family Disputes</a></li>
          </ul>
        </div>

      </nav>
    </aside>

    <!-- MAIN CONTENT -->
    <article class="main-content">

      <div class="intro">
        <p>Estate disputes can destroy relationships and drain inheritances. These are the most common flashpoints for family conflict.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Dispute 1 -->
      <div class="reason-card" id="reason-1">
        <div class="reason-header">
          <div class="reason-number">1</div>
        </div>
        <h2 class="reason-title">Unequal shares between siblings</h2>
        <p><strong>Conflict:</strong> "Why did she get more than me?" Even adult children expect equal treatment. Unequal shares breed resentment.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Dispute 2 -->
      <div class="reason-card" id="reason-2">
        <div class="reason-header">
          <div class="reason-number">2</div>
        </div>
        <h2 class="reason-title">The new spouse vs the children</h2>
        <p><strong>Conflict:</strong> A late remarriage often leaves children fearing their inheritance will go to a step-parent they barely know.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Dispute 3 -->
      <div class="reason-card" id="reason-3">
        <div class="reason-header">
          <div class="reason-number">3</div>
        </div>
        <h2 class="reason-title">Who gets the family home</h2>
        <p><strong>Conflict:</strong> Multiple beneficiaries with emotional attachments to the property — but only one can keep it.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Dispute 4 -->
      <div class="reason-card" id="reason-4">
        <div class="reason-header">
          <div class="reason-number">4</div>
        </div>
        <h2 class="reason-title">Executor favouring themselves</h2>
        <p><strong>Conflict:</strong> When the executor is also a beneficiary, other family members may suspect self-dealing.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Dispute 5 -->
      <div class="reason-card" id="reason-5">
        <div class="reason-header">
          <div class="reason-number">5</div>
        </div>
        <h2 class="reason-title">Sentimental items with no clear owner</h2>
        <p><strong>Conflict:</strong> The will covered the money, but who gets mum's engagement ring? Dad's war medals? Family photos?</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Dispute 6 -->
      <div class="reason-card" id="reason-6">
        <div class="reason-header">
          <div class="reason-number">6</div>
        </div>
        <h2 class="reason-title">Secret debts emerging</h2>
        <p><strong>Conflict:</strong> The estate is smaller than expected because of debts no one knew about. Beneficiaries blame each other.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Dispute 7 -->
      <div class="reason-card" id="reason-7">
        <div class="reason-header">
          <div class="reason-number">7</div>
        </div>
        <h2 class="reason-title">One child provided care, others didn't</h2>
        <p><strong>Conflict:</strong> The caregiver expects more. The absent siblings think they deserve equal shares regardless.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Dispute 8 -->
      <div class="reason-card" id="reason-8">
        <div class="reason-header">
          <div class="reason-number">8</div>
        </div>
        <h2 class="reason-title">Loans that were (or weren't) repaid</h2>
        <p><strong>Conflict:</strong> "Dad gave you $50,000 for your house — that should come out of your share." Undocumented loans cause wars.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Dispute 9 -->
      <div class="reason-card" id="reason-9">
        <div class="reason-header">
          <div class="reason-number">9</div>
        </div>
        <h2 class="reason-title">Business succession disputes</h2>
        <p><strong>Conflict:</strong> One child worked in the family business for years. Others want their share of its value.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Dispute 10 -->
      <div class="reason-card" id="reason-10">
        <div class="reason-header">
          <div class="reason-number">10</div>
        </div>
        <h2 class="reason-title">Missing or suspicious wills</h2>
        <p><strong>Conflict:</strong> A new will appears that benefits one person significantly. Others claim it's forged or obtained through manipulation.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- CTA Section -->
      <section class="cta-section">
        <div class="cta-inner">
          <h2>Clear instructions and open conversations can prevent these conflicts</h2>
          <p>Don't leave your family to fight over what you meant. Make it clear now.</p>
          <a href="/planning-tools/checklists/preparation" class="cta-button">Start Your Will Checklist →</a>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Sources -->
      <div class="sources">
        <h3>Sources</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Australian Law Reform Commission — Family Provision Claims</li>
          <li>State Trustees Victoria — Estate Disputes Research</li>
          <li>NSW Trustee & Guardian — Contested Wills Statistics</li>
          <li>Maurice Blackburn Lawyers — Family Dispute Trends</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

    </article>

  </div>
</main>

<Footer />

<style>
  * {
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    box-sizing: border-box;
  }

  body {
    font-family: 'Inter', -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, sans-serif;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: #2c3338;
    background: #ffffff;
  }

  /* Hero Section */
  .hero {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, #1a2e44 0%, #2a4560 100%);
    padding: 80px 64px;
    color: white;
  }

  .hero-inner {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .hero-badge {
    display: inline-block;
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.15);
    padding: 8px 16px;
    border-radius: 20px;
    font-size: 14px;
    font-weight: 500;
    margin-bottom: 20px;
  }

  .hero h1 {
    font-size: 48px;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-bottom: 20px;
    line-height: 1.2;
  }

  .hero-subtitle {
    font-size: 18px;
    line-height: 1.6;
    opacity: 0.95;
  }

  /* Stat Bar */
  .stat-bar {
    background: #faf6e9;
    padding: 24px 64px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #e2e2e2;
  }

  .stat-bar-inner {
    max-width: 900px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
    gap: 60px;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .stat-item {
    text-align: center;
  }

  .stat-number {
    font-family: 'Source Serif 4', Georgia, serif;
    font-size: 36px;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #1a2e44;
  }

  .stat-label {
    font-size: 13px;
    color: #7a7a7a;
    margin-top: 4px;
  }

  /* Content Wrapper */
  .content-wrapper {
    display: flex;
    max-width: 1200px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 40px 24px;
    gap: 40px;
  }

  /* Sidebar */
  .top10-sidebar {
    width: 240px;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .sidebar-nav {
    position: sticky;
    top: 100px;
  }

  .sidebar-section {
    margin-bottom: 32px;
  }

  .sidebar-section:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .sidebar-title {
    font-family: Inter, -apple-system, sans-serif;
    font-size: 13px;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: #c9a227;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    margin: 0 0 12px 0;
  }

  .sidebar-nav ul {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 4px;
  }

  .sidebar-link {
    font-family: Inter, -apple-system, sans-serif;
    font-size: 14px;
    color: #4a4a4a;
    text-decoration: none;
    border-bottom: none;
    padding: 6px 8px;
    border-radius: 6px;
    display: block;
    transition: all 0.2s;
    line-height: 1.4;
  }

  .sidebar-num {
    display: inline-block;
    width: 20px;
    height: 20px;
    background: #1a2e44;
    color: white;
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 600;
    border-radius: 4px;
    text-align: center;
    line-height: 20px;
    margin-right: 8px;
  }

  .sidebar-link.active {
    background: #faf6e9;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: #1a2e44;
  }

  .sidebar-link.disabled {
    color: #9ca3af;
    opacity: 0.6;
    cursor: not-allowed;
  }

  .sidebar-link:not(.disabled):not(.active):hover {
    background: #f5f5f5;
    color: #1a2e44;
  }

  /* Main Content */
  .main-content {
    flex: 1;
    max-width: 800px;
  }

  .intro {
    background: #f9f6f1;
    border-left: 4px solid #c9a227;
    padding: 24px;
    margin-bottom: 40px;
    border-radius: 8px;
  }

  .intro p {
    font-size: 16px;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: #4b5563;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }

  .intro p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  /* Reason Cards */
  .reason-card {
    background: white;
    border: 2px solid #e5e2dd;
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 32px;
    margin-bottom: 24px;
  }

  .reason-header {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 16px;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }

  .reason-number {
    width: 48px;
    height: 48px;
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, #1a2e44 0%, #2a4560 100%);
    border-radius: 10px;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    font-size: 24px;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: white;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .reason-title {
    font-size: 24px;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #1a2e44;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }

  .reason-card p {
    font-size: 16px;
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: #4b5563;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }

  /* CTA Section */
  .cta-section {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, #1a2e44 0%, #2a4560 100%);
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 48px 32px;
    text-align: center;
    margin: 40px 0;
  }

  .cta-inner h2 {
    font-size: 28px;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: white;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }

  .cta-inner p {
    font-size: 18px;
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.9);
    margin-bottom: 24px;
  }

  .cta-button {
    display: inline-block;
    background: #c9a227;
    color: white;
    padding: 14px 32px;
    border-radius: 8px;
    font-size: 16px;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: background 0.2s;
  }

  .cta-button:hover {
    background: #b08920;
  }

  /* Sources */
  .sources {
    max-width: 900px;
    margin: 40px auto 0;
    padding: 40px 0;
    border-top: 1px solid #e2e2e2;
  }

  .sources h3 {
    font-size: 14px;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: #7a7a7a;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }

  .sources ul {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 8px 24px;
  }

  .sources li {
    font-size: 13px;
    color: #7a7a7a;
  }

  /* Responsive */
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .top10-sidebar {
      display: none;
    }

    .stat-bar-inner {
      gap: 40px;
    }

    .stat-number {
      font-size: 28px;
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .hero {
      padding: 60px 32px;
    }

    .hero h1 {
      font-size: 36px;
    }

    .stat-bar {
      padding: 20px 32px;
    }

    .content-wrapper {
      padding: 40px 32px;
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .hero {
      padding: 40px 20px;
    }

    .hero h1 {
      font-size: 28px;
    }

    .hero-subtitle {
      font-size: 16px;
    }

    .stat-bar {
      padding: 20px 20px;
    }

    .content-wrapper {
      padding: 32px 20px;
    }

    .reason-card {
      padding: 24px;
    }

    .reason-title {
      font-size: 20px;
    }

    .cta-section {
      padding: 32px 20px;
    }

    .cta-inner h2 {
      font-size: 24px;
    }
  }
</style>

</body>
</html>
